post: {'type': 'con', 'text': 'The Federal Government \\(US\\) has no constitutional authority to regulate what citizens choose to put in their bodies. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Something being illegal makes the entire area "tainted." Talking about how to do something illegal is seen as encouraging said activity, and "sending the wrong signals."'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Making things safer will benefit all users, while a false sense of safety only applies to a minority. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'According to the [Global Commission on Drug Policy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Global_Commission_on_Drug_Policy), the war on drugs was a failure. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Justifying a ban because it provides people with more autonomy is an inherent contradiction. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'When the government legalizes something, it \\(unintentionally\\) sends the message that the substance is acceptable and a legitimate form of recreation. This may encourage people to become involved in drug taking.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are more effective policies than legalizing drug use to challenge drug abuse.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Illegally acquired date rape drugs could be even more dangerous to victims, as they may be cut with dangerous chemicals. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Just because there are other systematic racial issues does not mean we cannot challenge this particular racist law.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'They would have died on those drugs whether or not they were legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs hinders scientific and, in particular, medical progress.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Prohibition clearly isn't enough either, and all but ensures that honest education and information becomes impossible, making it exaggerated and ineffective."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs relate frequently with [suicide attempts](https://www.encyclopedia.com/education/encyclopedias-almanacs-transcripts-and-maps/accidents-and-injuries-drugs). So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Reducing the number of users and frequency of use is just a means to an end. The end goal is to reduce harms created by drug use. It's perfectly possible to increase use and have less overall harm. So all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Although social prejudice may remain, addicts could seek help far easier if there were no fear of legal repercussions.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "A society where everyone consumes moderate amounts of drugs wouldn't be much different than the societies of today. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is little medical discrimination for those who use legal harmful substances such as alcohol or tobacco.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While some might overestimate the revenue, there still will be revenue. If it is 1/2 or 1/3 of those naive estimates, it is still revenue, and it still increases the government coffers.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If the primary goal is defeating drug dealing and cartels, the most effective way would be just ceasing drug use by everyone. With the "added bonus" that without drug use people will also be healthier and richer. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Regulations that prohibit working under the influence of alcohol can trivially be expanded to include all drugs. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If you plan to drug someone with the intent of raping them, you're also able to get a hold of the something as ubiquitous as a benzodiazepine."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Designer drugs already exist, are legal and work this angle. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug cartels destabilize Latin America. With legalization they would disappear and Latin America would gain stability.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is biased against those with mental illness. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The logic of this argument would necessitate prohibition of alcohol, along with cigarettes, prescription painkillers, household cleaning products, motor vehicles, power tools; and anything a person may use to end their life consciously or accidentally. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Under legalisation, self-injection as a route of administration may be reduced, as safer alternatives become available.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The illegal trade is already there. The legal trade would just drain their customer base. For criminal trade to survive in those conditions it would have to have either cheaper prices or better product. These are not easily achieved agains big corporations. At least the competition would seriously damage their overheads.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If an individual is already addicted, that would indicate they already have regular access to the drug.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's not a given that the low well-being of drug users' families are a result of the drug use. The confounding variable is likely mental health issues. It's possible \\(and sometimes preferable\\) to solve the mental health issues, while not stopping the drug use."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Due to abundance and normalization, people could enjoy other drugs like the enjoy a glass of wine. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Currently medical professionals can and do discriminate against those who use substances simply because they're illegal. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Bettering education surrounding date rape and the drugs used for it would improve levels of prevention. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition consumes a considerable portion of public spending.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A higher number of drugs users will create more work for the accident and emergency paramedic services that have to deal with people who have overdosed due to improper usage.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalizing drugs does not imply you may use them on someone without their permission. It's already illegal to give someone else a narcotic they were not prescribed, even though the drug itself is legal. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Rational discussion of the costs and benefits of smoking tobacco and negative ads led a lot of people to decide it isn't worth doing. All without prohibiting it."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Tracing a car owner by his license plate after causing a severe accident with people killed does not undo the accident either. But it creates a moral barrier for people, so they think twice before doing such a hit and run. Same goes for traceable drugs. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's people's own choice whether to be moral or not. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalised, drug users could be less likely to leave dangerous paraphernalia \\(broken pipes, syringes, etc.\\) behind in public places as the fear of criminal penalties for the possession of drug paraphernalia would no longer be an issue. This would lessen risk of disease and injury. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs means that they are taken, and disposed of, more safely and cautiously than in the current environment.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Date-rape drugs are controlled presently. The current prohibition has not hindered the occurrence of date rape.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Addiction treatment isn't actually very expensive or costly, and is likely to be clinically simpler to resolve than is widely assumed."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization does not treat addicts, treatment and prevention of the addiction do. Both of which can be done with drugs remaining illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Organized crime would find themselves without a cash-flow and resort to much more violent kidnapping and extortion. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Organized crime would find themselves without a cash-flow and resort to much more violent kidnapping and extortion. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Currently medical professionals can and do discriminate against those who use substances simply because they're illegal. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In a free society, drug users must be free to share their perspective with others, and other people must be free to decide for themselves how they want to act.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A large portion of the public is irresponsible. Giving everyone the opportunity to use \\(or abuse\\) drugs would have negative consequences on these individuals.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There will be less smuggling and less drug-caused conflict. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The anxiety induced by the threat of arrest can be a cause for the violent paranoia episodes some users experience while under the influence emotion enhancing substances.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs may lead to children trying and becoming involved with drugs at a younger age.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Governments would be able to check what cutting agents are used within the drugs, meaning they will be safer as potentially harmful cutting agents would be banned. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing all drugs will be seen as a sign of the government/authority giving up on protecting people from the harm they could do, to themselves and others, through poorly selected drug use.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The issue with these drugs is that it's possible for someone to ingest it unknowingly, after someone dropped them in their drink etc. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Chronic cocaine use causes [multiple damaging health effects](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cocaine#Chronic) to the user, combined with an increased tolerance, leading to a snowball effect of deteriorating health.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are still many other ways in which criminal associations could take advantage of the situation and legally start selling drugs or exploiting the farmers as they do now.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[The Controlled Substances Act](https://www.dea.gov/druginfo/ds.shtml), prohibits Schedule 1 substances \\(such as Cannabis\\), which forces patients to either break the law or use more harmful/addictive substances that are inferior medicine. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "A change in the law to deny all those who suffer self inflicted physical ill-health or mental trauma, including junkies, free access to the N.H.S., would, or at least should jolt the pleasure seekers out of their surreal world in which they enjoy a ''free ride''."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Some drugs will lead to people having hallucinations or becoming violent. In these instances, individuals may be a danger to themselves or others. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs such as PCP have caused [grotesque instances](https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/real-life-stories/rapper-killed-girlfriend-chewed-up-11566075) of violence by the user onto other individuals.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Education and information campaigns could be funded by taxes on the drugs themselves. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A more substantial part of society will be exposed to the harmful and dangerous side effects of drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "As long as the taxes don't surpass the higher costs of the black market businesses, there is no reason to believe that legal drugs would be more expensive. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'They may lose their job and thus stop contributing to society and paying taxes.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs could be legalised in government shops in which they could be administered through government pharmacists. This would allow governments to control access, much like the [Swedish alcohol trade](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Systembolaget).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Affordable drugs will more likely lessen the negative impacts of drug use, as overall users would be less likely to abuse substances due to psychological distress caused by financial instability.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'It will destroy jobs for drug enforcement agencies, lawyers, judges, police, prison wardens. There is a whole industry depending on it.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Established entities selling drugs would almost certainly not engage in gun battles on the streets over "[turf](https://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=Turf)".'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Under the influence of drugs, users are more likely to commit immoral acts.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Even if criminals are able to offer drugs at lower prices, people would turn to legal drugs because they would not risk prison and they would be sure of the quality of what they're buying. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'That correlation is not affected by their legality. So, legalization will not make it worse unless it causes the price to go down. Given the emphasis many put on drug taxes as an argument in favor of legalization, that seems unlikely.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is not fair to solve such a problem by prohibiting heroin use for everyone. It should be solved as a problem on its own. This could mean anything from forbidding heroin addicts to have children \\(or parents to use heroin\\), to forming organisations for helping such families. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "As this is also true under prohibition, it's an argument for proper education, not an argument against legalization. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'They would have died on those drugs whether or not they were legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Drug users will encourage other people, who do not know how to handle drugs and/or aren't smart and/or mature enough to try it. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "An Indian based study shows that substance consumption highly relate to [juvenile delinquency.](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4919962/) That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are still many other ways in which criminal associations could take advantage of the situation and legally start selling drugs or exploiting the farmers as they do now.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Illegal drug producers and dealers use violence against police and competition. This just doesn't happen in legal businesses. The causes for this is also obvious. A legal business using violence will get fines and possibly be banned from participating in the legal market, and as such is a non-starter. I believe all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The first [anti-cocaine laws](http://www.drugpolicy.org/issues/brief-history-drug-war) in the early 1900s were directed at black men in the South.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs would significantly decrease social stigma and discrimination against users who have been incarcerated for employment and education opportunities.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many constitutions and legal frameworks promote personal autonomy. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "[Ricin](https://emergency.cdc.gov/agent/ricin/facts.asp), a highly poisonous substance, is created from castor beans. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Job security in an immoral industry should not be an argument for maintaining the status quo.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'One solution for recreational availability of such drugs could be to require that they emit an unmistakable coloring or odour/taste when dissolved in a drink.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the same way that people sign contracts in which they voluntarily limit their freedom for a certain amount of time, a person who chooses freely to take drugs is choosing to limit their self-control freely. In either case, the initial choice is still a free choice. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The anxiety induced by the threat of arrest can be a cause for the violent paranoia episodes some users experience while under the influence emotion enhancing substances.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'People may drive under the influence of drugs or make other decisions with public consequences.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Historically, the US government has only permitted research which [supports their agenda](https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2015/08/18/feds-limit-research-marijuana-medical-use/31547557/) of prohibition. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Entheogenic drugs](https://maps.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=5468), such as psychedelics, have been used throughout human history for many benefits in evolutionary growth and cognitive development.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If drugs were legalized, the prison system would be less over-crowded, which is a [significant issue](https://www.prisonpolicy.org/reports/pie2019.html) in the US.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization of drugs will make people aware of their consequences \\(having a prospectus like medicine with known pros and cons - like marijuana for medical usage\\). So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legal drugs would not be the only option; there may still be a market of illegal drugs, for example if it is cheaper than the legal choice.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If legalized, the users wouldn't have the same incentive to rid themselves of the evidence as quickly as possible."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will allow access to drugs to be graded based on risks taking them, meaning more addictive and harmful drugs could be made less available and desirable by taxing them accordingly.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The cost of alcohol was roughly 3 times higher during prohibition than compared to previous prices \\([pg. 7](http://www.nber.org/papers/w3675.pdf)\\). So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of all drugs could make people live and learn life as it is. Bad decisions are a part of life.'}
